last_episode_to_air.name: UFC
last_episode_to_air.overview: The UFC offers the boys exclusive behind-the-scenes access with some of MMA's biggest icons... if they compete in the Octagon in front of a live crowd.

name: Rob & Romesh Vs
overview: After the success of their 2017 show with heavyweight boxing champion Anthony Joshua, funny men Rob Beckett and Romesh Ranganathan are back to interview more celebrities from the worlds of sport, entertainment, fashion, and more.

episodes.name: Usain Bolt
episodes.overview: In the first episode, Rob and Romesh hook up with legend Usain Bolt in his Jamaican homeland. But before they do, Rob takes Romesh on a Lightning-Bolt themed trip around the island. Will their friendship survive the tour?

episodes.name: The NFL
episodes.overview: As Super Bowl fever takes over the world, Rob and Romesh go on a mission to learn all about America's best loved sport.

episodes.name: Fashion
episodes.overview: Rob Beckett and Romesh Ranganathan go on a mission to learn all about the world of fashion.

episodes.name: Superstar DJs
episodes.overview: Rob and Romesh's next stop in their journey of discovery leads them into the hot and loud world of Superstar DJs.

episodes.name: Country Music
episodes.overview: Rob and Romesh get singing tips from country star Shania Twain.

episodes.name: Anthony Joshua
episodes.overview: Rob Becket and Romesh Ranganathan are off to catch up with the Heavyweight Champion of The World, Anthony Joshua.

episodes.name: Ballet
episodes.overview: Best friends Rob Beckett and Romesh Ranganathan are back as they dive into the world of ballet, including roles in a real performance of Swan Lake.

episodes.name: NBA Basketball
episodes.overview: Rob and Romesh learn about basketball, a journey that takes them from the street courts of Los Angeles to the iconic Staples Center itself.

episodes.name: Cricket: South Africa
episodes.overview: The guys go to South Africa to follow England's cricket team. There's commentary, a lesson with Kevin Pietersen - and even a safari.

episodes.name: Cricket: The Test
episodes.overview: Part two of the tour for cricket newbies Rob and Romesh as they follow England's Test series. The match comes to a dramatic finale.

episodes.name: Art
episodes.overview: Rob & Romesh are back to dip their toes into the unknown, as the duo become budding artists tasked with creating an exhibition for the Saatchi Gallery.

episodes.name: Golf
episodes.overview: Rob and Romesh are learning all about golf. It's Rob's new hobby and he wants Romesh to become his new golfing buddy. On their journey they play their first ever round at the iconic St Andrews. Have a golfing lesson from Olympic Champion Justin Rose. Before each of them get to tee off at the world famous BMW PGA Championship - live on Sky Sports.

episodes.name: Drag
episodes.overview: For the final show of the series, Rob and Romesh will become Drag Queens. They'll be getting a full make from the stars of Drag Race - The Vivienne and Baga Chipz. They meet icon Michelle Visage to find their drag personas. Before each of them perform their very own drag routine in front of live audience.

episodes.name: Andy Murray
episodes.overview: In this very special edition, Rob and Romesh will be hanging out with British sporting legend, Sir Andy Murray. They'll catch up with him as he models his new sports wear range, before being pushed to their limits in a tennis training session and Andy's favourite hobby, road cycling. Their mission is to try to get to know what makes the greatest British tennis player of all time really tick.

episodes.name: Team GB (1)
episodes.overview: It's Olympic year, so Rob and Romesh try their hand at weightlifting, hockey and slalom canoe to see if they too could be part of Team GB.

episodes.name: Team GB (2)
episodes.overview: Rob and Romesh continue their Olympic adventure as they try clay pigeon shooting, gymnastics and athletics, with help from special teachers.

episodes.name: Almost Everything
episodes.overview: Highlights from across the series as mates Rob Beckett and Romesh Ranganathan try their hand at everything from art to golf and tennis to drag performance.

episodes.name: Strongmen
episodes.overview: Rob and Romesh will be witnessing insane strength up close as they take on the world of Strongman. On their journey they head to Iceland to train with former champion Magnus Ver Magnusson. All with the aim of competing one on one at the Arnold Sports Festival to find out which of the two is the strongest.

episodes.name: The West End
episodes.overview: Rob and Romesh are on a mission to crack the world of musicals and land a role in a blockbuster show in London's West End. With the help of Samantha Barks - who stars as Elsa in Frozen The Musical - she guides the boys with some tips and pulls some strings to sort out an audition for one of the West End's biggest productions - Disney's The Lion King.

episodes.name: Restaurants: First Course
episodes.overview: Rob and Romesh are opening their own restaurant! In the first of a special two parter, this week they learn all about the restaurant industry to find out what they will do for their own establishment. With the help of Michelin starred chef Tom Kerridge, the lads learn everything from Front of House to Foraging, with the show culminating as the boys become chefs during a real service in a real restaurant.

episodes.name: Restaurants: Second Course
episodes.overview: Rob and Romesh's journey into the restaurant business continues... and this week it's opening night! Having to do everything from find a location to shopping for their ingredients, this two parter culminates with the boys opening London's very first Hip Hop Curry House - Robandroms.

episodes.name: Magic In Vegas
episodes.overview: The boys are invited by Penn & Teller to join Vegas' longest-running residency show and have just three days to pull their act together.

episodes.name: K-Pop
episodes.overview: Comedians Rob Beckett and Romesh Ranganathan enter the world of the music phenomenon of K-Pop. They start their journey at a sold-out NCT Dream gig at Wembley Arena, then head to South Korea to learn about the genre.

episodes.name: Crufts
episodes.overview: With Rob and Romesh both now dog owners, they're entering this year's Crufts to see if their new best friends can learn a thing or two.

episodes.name: Classical Music
episodes.overview: The London Philharmonic Orchestra are performing a year-long residency at the Royal Festival Hall... and they've invited Rob and Romesh to join them.

episodes.name: The Three Lions
episodes.overview: Rob Beckett and Romesh Ranganathan meet the stars of the England football team before the World Cup, and hang out with Gareth Southgate.

episodes.name: Lapland
episodes.overview: Rob and Romesh head to Lapland for Christmas, where they try their luck at a range of festive-themed tasks featuring elves, reindeer, magic and Santa Claus to see if there's one activity that they have the Christmas spirit for.

episodes.name: F1 Monaco: Part 1
episodes.overview: In preparation for the Monaco Grand Prix, Rob and Romesh meet Lewis Hamilton and join F1 team Mercedes to learn how to be a member of the pit crew.

episodes.name: F1 Monaco: Part 2
episodes.overview: Rob Beckett and Romesh Ranganathan continue their Formula 1 journey in Monaco, hanging out with driver George Russell, before Rob finally takes his manual driving test.

episodes.name: Hollywood Stunts
episodes.overview: Rob Beckett and Romesh Ranganathan take on more challenges, beginning by heading off to Los Angeles to throw themselves into the world of Hollywood stuntmen. They meet The Fall Guy stars Ryan Gosling and Emily Blunt before training with the film's director David Leitch, then head back to the UK to perform a stunt on Hollyoaks.

episodes.name: Heavy Metal
episodes.overview: Scottish band Bleed from Within try to educate Rob Beckett and Romesh Ranganathan in the ways of the headbanger in time for a surprise performance of Metallica's Enter Sandman at the Download festival in front of 4,000 fans. The boys also get some extra tips from US rock stars Wheatus and Queens of the Stone Age.

episodes.name: UFC
episodes.overview: The UFC offers the boys exclusive behind-the-scenes access with some of MMA's biggest icons... if they compete in the Octagon in front of a live crowd.

episodes.name: Wildlife
episodes.overview: The duo go behind the lens and test out their photography skills as part of the Natural History Museum's Wildlife Photographer of the Year.
